summary:
I am a retired Australian Ambassador living in The Netherlands who helps talented young people secure Masters and PhD admissions, internships, and jobs. I also lecture and provide Workshops on  Getting a Job After Graduation to groups such as Women in Innovation and Leadership, the Honours Class of Amsterdam Medical Centre, The Hague Municipality, the University of Applied Sciences, and Leiden Universityâ€™s Future Ready Coaching Academy. 

Young people certainly need help in a labour market upended by the corona pandemic and marked by extraordinary levels of competition. 

Unfortunately, there is a lot of misinformation and plain rubbish out there; much of it from people who might mean well, but have never sat on a Selection Panel in their life.

Helping young people is a lot of fun, keeps the little grey cells ticking over, and has a hugely positive effect on people's lives. Among other things, my charges have cracked 17 major international Universities, prestigious US think tanks, and 6 diplomatic services. 

Which beats playing golf...ðŸ˜‚
